1 olive oil
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bottle balsamic glaze
2 tomato
1 bag herbs
1 lemon
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
½ packet Cow's Milk Feta
3 mini baguette
1 packet Akaroa Cold Smoked Salmon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Slice mini baguettes on an angle into 1cm-thick slices. In a large bowl,
combine garlic & herb seasoning and a 1/4 cup of olive oil. Add baguette
slices and toss until well coated.
• Divide baguette slices between two lined oven trays and spread out evenly.
Bake until golden and crisp, 5-6 minutes.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice tomato. Crumble cheese (see ingredients). Finely
chop herbs.

• Sprinkle 1/2 the crumbled cheese over 1/2 the crostini. Tear or slice Akaroa
smoked salmon into small pieces and lay over cheese-topped crostinis.
• Zest lemon and cut in half. Sprinkle lemon zest over salmon-topped
crostinis. Season with black pepper and squeeze over some lemon juice.

TIP: Roll or fold the salmon pieces to give some height!

• Spread creamy pesto dressing over remaining crostinis. Top with sliced
tomato and sprinkle with remaining crumbled cheese. Drizzle with
balsamic glaze.

• Arrange crostini on a serving platter and garnish with herbs to serve. Enjoy!